transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra, Escort Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'd like to know why y'all took $40 and something few cents out of my account.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir. So yeah, we can take a look at the prescription and see how this is organized.

Speaker 2: Bear with me while I pull up your account, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alright. Could I please get your full name and date of birth, please, under the prescription?

Speaker 1: Scott Matthews, 12.7 of 1974.

Speaker 2: Thanks, Scott.

Speaker 1: You there?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. Sorry, I'm just looking at the details from the doctor.

Speaker 1: I was classifying it. I didn't hear nothing.

Speaker 2: I know. I can be quiet sometimes. Sorry about that.

Speaker 1: Alright. So I see here the initial prescription was written in November.

Speaker 2: That was for the 100 mg Viagra.

Speaker 1: Is that right?

Speaker 2: Does that sound accurate? Okay.

Speaker 1: It looks like what the doctor did is it wrote it with refills, okay?

Speaker 2: She wrote it with refills every two months.

Speaker 1: This is not required or obligated.

Speaker 2: I have seen cases in this where with the lower quantities they'll do this for patient convenience,

Speaker 1: but obviously it comes to surprise if you didn't see it in their notes.

Speaker 2: Scott, this is not a subscription.

Speaker 1: You're not required to get this every month.

Speaker 2: If you wanted, you could pause the prescription where you won't receive these monthly,

Speaker 1: and that would allow you to call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 2: I'd rather do that than have a surprise like this.

Speaker 1: Sure, sure. I completely understand.

Speaker 2: So I'll go ahead and put that pause on there for you, okay?

Speaker 1: It's going to be paused until August 1st.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alright, you're all set.

Speaker 2: Alright, Scott, yeah, if you want an order before that, just make sure you give us a call.

Speaker 1: So I've got an order coming in right now?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir, you do.

Speaker 1: That is scheduled right now.

Speaker 2: It looks like it's set to be delivered middle of next week.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
